'''Spencer List''' (born April 6, 1998) is an American [[child actor]]. List is best known from the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] show ''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]'' where he played a mysterious mute child in the episode "[[Inner Child (Fringe)|Inner Child]]". He has also been on ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'' where he played the son of [[Leland Orser]]'s character Kevin Walker. List appeared in Jack Ketchum's ''Offspring'' in 2009.
==Personal life== List was born in [[Florida]], but moved to [[New York]] at age of 4. He began acting at an early age, both alone and also with his twin sister [[Peyton Roi List|Peyton]]. List has appeared in over four hundred commercial advertisements in various formats for various companies.
List currently lives in the state of New York. His younger brother, Phoenix, and twin sister [[Peyton Roi List|Peyton]] are both actors and models.
